AUDIO: 'dancing in a sea of flowers slowly moving her hands. And then over here, if you\'re just doing text to video, you can also specify the width and height over here. So in order to do that, you do need to disconnect these noodles. So,'

[12:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'let me just disconnect these two so that we can adjust the width and height. And because vase 14B can generate up to 1280 x 720, let\'s actually do this. I\'m going to set this to 1280x 720. And then the'

[12:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'length of your video is basically how long you want the video to be. So, right now, this is 81 frames divided by 16 frames per second over here, which is roughly I can\'t do public math. Let\'s'

[12:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just plug this in Google. and we get 5 seconds. Now to make this a bit faster, let\'s just set this to like 49 for example, which should give us around 3 seconds of video. And then it plugs this'

[13:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'into this K sampler component, which basically generates the video. Now, there are a few more things you need to note. So for number of steps, basically this is how many iterations you want the AI to go through before giving you the output video. So in general, the more'

[13:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'steps you have, the higher quality the video will be, but at a certain point, you\'re going to get diminishing returns. So, it seems like the sweet spot here is 20 steps. And if you want to make this a bit faster, you can also decrease the'

[13:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'step count to like 15, for example, to make this run faster at the sacrifice of some quality. And then CFG is how literally you want the AI to follow your prompt over here. So, if you have a high'

[13:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'CFG value, it\'s going to follow this prompt really literally, whereas if you have a low CFG value, it can be more creative and add some elements in the video which you have not specified. And then sampler name. This is just the'

[13:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'algorithm that\'s used to generate the video. And then seed is also really important. This is basically the starting point. So if you have all the settings the same and you keep the same seed, you\'re going to generate the exact same video as before. If you want a'

[14:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'slightly different video, you can set this to randomize. But for now, I\'m just going to leave this as fixed. And then one more important thing to note is this note over here. Because we have turned'

[14:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on this cause vid Laura which helps us speed up our generation. We actually don\'t need to run this for as many steps. So it says over here just four to six steps is fine. Plus we also need to'

[14:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'set the cfg to one. So let\'s set the step count to four and then the cfg to one. And this is especially important if you have a GPU with low VRAM. This Cosvid Laura is a lifesaver and it\'s'

[14:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to speed up your generation by a lot. And that\'s pretty much it. So, let\'s click run and see what that gives us. And afterwards, here we go. Indeed, we have a girl dancing in a sea of'

